{ White's move order allows Black to play ...Bg4. Generally speaking, one can say that the trade of Black's bishop for the white f3-knight leads to positions that are a bit dryer and easier to handle for both. It is not really better or worse, but rather a matter of taste what one prefers. }
10. Qb3
{ This is something we should always be on the lookout for when moving our bishop from c8 early on, but more often than not, Black can sacrifice b7 for activity. }
10... Nbd7 11. Qxb7 O-O 12. Qb3 Bxf3 13. gxf3 c5
{ Black has very active play for the pawn and White struggles to find a long-term safe place for the king. }
