19. Na4 Ng7 { 19...f6  20.Ng4  Rae8  is also reasonable. } 20. Nc5 f6
{ A nice idea. } 21. Ng4 Bxg4 22. hxg4 f5
{ This is a very nice way to create counterplay. After: } 23. gxf5 gxf5
{ We will get play on the kingside with ...Rf6 next. } *

