9... Qd8 10. e4 c6 11. Qb6
{ Absolutely the only move, as otherwise the pin would just win a piece. }
11... cxd5 { Very strong.   11...Qxb6  12.Nxb6  is White's idea. } 12. Qxa7
dxe4 13. Nd2 Bb4
{ Black has given up an exchange, but the initiative is very strong. The computers indicate that White can survive to equality, but nobody would voluntarily enter this as White. }
14. Qxb7 { White has to risk this in order to survive. } 14... Bxd2+ 15. Kxd2
O-O 16. Qxe4 Qa5+ 17. Kd1
{ And here many other moves, such as ...Re8 or ....Qa4+, also gives Black decent play. }
17... Bb3+ { The most direct. } 18. axb3 Qxa1+ 19. Ke2 Qxb2+ 20. Kf3 Qxb3+ 21.
Bd3 g6
{ Unfortunately our initiative was only enough to equalize, but White had to play better than Black to get here! }
