8. Be2 b5 9. Ne5
{ Basically the only real way to play the position - White desperately needs some counterplay in the centre and on the kingside. }
9... Be7 { Simple development. } 10. Bf3 Bb7 11. O-O O-O
{ This was very solid for Black and he soon took over in L'Ami-Vallejo Pons, Douglas 2019. But do note that we delay castling until White has castled as well, as any sort of kingside pawn storm is now a lot less appealing. }
