9. Nxd4 Bg4
{ Not letting White develop calmly. This in my opinion puts the most pressure on White, although it's really a matter of taste. }
10. Be2 Bxe2
{ 10...Bh3  looks very tempting, but after  11.g4  the black bishop runs a clear risk of getting stuck at  h3  . }
11. Ncxe2 Bb4+
{ Important, to create a tiny bit of disharmony in White's camp. } 12. Kf1 O-O
13. Kg2 Qd7
{ We got a slight weakness on d5, but with White having played g3 and traded the light squared bishops there is plenty of room for counterplay. The White knights are also somewhat stupidly placed, making the position all in all balanced. }
