9... c6 { Continuing with our usual setup. } 10. Bf4
{ The simplest way for White. With the knight on e2 instead of f3 it will be very difficult for us to stop the central plan of f3 followed by e4. It might look like a loss of tempo for White, but the tempo gained by ...Be6 is not that relevant here @@StartBracket@@we rather want to trade it on f5 or g4!@@EndBracket@@ and we do not protect the d6-bishop with our queen anymore, meaning we will lose back another tempo doing that. }
10... Bxf4
{ 10...Qc7  11.O-O  O-O  12.f3  followed by  Qd2  and  Rae1  is similar. } 11.
Nxf4 O-O 12. O-O
{ Now the position of a slower nature, and there are plenty of moves for each side. I'll just give some exemplatory lines to give an impression of how it might develop. }
12... Re8 13. f3 Nf8 { Trying to improve the knight. } 14. Qd2 Ng6 15. Nxg6
hxg6 { This would be absolutely fine, with ...Bf5 coming next. } *

