10... Nxd5
{ Our next move would be to play ...c4, grabbing even more space on the queenside. }
11. Rc1 c4
{ A strategically interesting idea. We give up the centre, but our queenside pawns are rather potent. An additional point is that e4 isn't actually that scary, as it allows Nb4-d3. }
