{ The first move is obvious. Our entire idea of playing 3...a6 is to take on c4 next if White doesn't defend it, and here he didn't! }
5. Bg2 { Now Black has a very important choice. } 5... c5
{ The solid approach. We try to trade material in the centre. } 6. O-O cxd4 7.
Nxd4 Nf6
{ 7...e5?  8.Nf3  Qxd1  9.Rxd1  Compared to7. Qxd4, White got an extra move, Rd1, which we can't allow!  9...Nc6  10.Nbd2!  f6  11.Nxc4  Be6  12.b3  and Rd1 is a huge tempo to have gained here, as Nd6+ will soon be on the agenda! }
8. Qa4+
{ This is a very smart check. By moving the queen White stops our idea of playing ...e5 and trading queens. }
8... Qd7
{ 8...Nbd7  is unfortunately too slow:  9.Rd1!  e5?!  10.Nf5  followed by the very annoying Nd6+. }
9. Qxc4
