{ 10.Qd3  Bb7  is very similar. } 10... Bb7 11. Bxb7 Qxb7 12. a4
{ The critical way of playing, as we are now forced to put our b-pawn on a dark square. }
12... b4 13. Bg5
{ The bishop is actually White's worst piece here, as the knights are much better equipped at exploiting our queenside weaknesses. Therefore it is a good idea for White to play Bg5xf6 here. }
