6. Qb3
{ The critical move, trying to keep the pawn alive for a while and threatening b7! }
6... Bd7
{ An important move to remember! The check on a4 must be stopped later on.  6...Bb7?!  7.Bf4!  is a bit annoying.  7...c4  8.Qa4+!  is the difference compared to6...Bd7. }
7. Nc3 Nf6 8. e4
{ Now it gets fun!  8.Bf4  c4  again a good version with White having misplaced the bishop on f4. }
8... c4
{ 8...Nc6!?  is an interesting alternative that can lead to incredibly messy positions after  9.exd5  Nxd4  But I don't entirely trust it for Black.  8...cxd4?  9.Nxd4  Bc5  gives White time for  10.Be3  with the tactical trick  Qxb6  11.Qxb6  Bxb6  12.Nxe6  with a great advantage. }
