{ The position looks very complicated, but the most likely scenario is all the pawns on b6 and d4 for White and e4 and c4 for Black dropping off, leading to a balanced fight. }
11. Nd2 Nc6 { This hits the weakness on d4. } 12. b7 Rb8 13. Qxe4
{ Covering d4, but White is still not developing the kingside... } 13... Na5
{ 13...Nb4!?  is also interesting. } 14. Nxc4 Bc6 15. Qe3 Nxc4
