Bxc6 12. Qxc6
{ Now White is positionally winning with the backward c-pawn, the weak b5-pawn and the bishop pair. Luckily we have huge concrete counterplay! }
12... Bb4+ 13. Bd2
{ Traading off the bishops while still having to move the king. } 13... Bxd2+
14. Kxd2 bxa4 { Followed by castling and putting pressure along the b-file. } *

