{ The most natural move. White is getting ready to meet Nd7 with the unpleasant Ba5. }
12... Nxd2 { 12...Nd7  13.Ba5!  is slightly annoying. } 13. Qxd2 bxa4
{ Looks stupid, but with the rook having left a1 it makes a lot of sense. While White recaptures the pawn we can put pressure along the b-file. I believe we do not have any problems at all here, the only issue being that it might be a little bit dry.  13...Nd7  is also possible of course, but I prefer the more direct idea of capturing on a4. }
14. Qb4 { Trying to disturb our coordination. } 14... Bc6 15. Ne5 a5
{ A useful inclusion! } 16. Qc4 Bd5 17. Qxa4 Ra7
{ This is a cute manouver. The b2-pawn is actually a major weakness in White's position! }
18. f3 Rb7 19. Nd3 Qh4+
{ This is very annoying. Nf2 is not possible due to the b2-pawn hanging. } 20.
g3 Qh5 { Picking up the f3-pawn. } *

