7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O Bb7 9. b3 a5
{ This is a nice idea against b3 when the knight is on d2 rather than c3.  9...Ne4  with the usual follow up of ...Nd7, ...f5, ...Qe7, etc is also fine, but when given a chance we should try to put maximum pressure on White! }
10. a4 { This would weaken the b4-square too much. } 10... Na6
{ This is another reason for delaying ...Nbd7. The knight will be super strong on b4! }
