{ This is actually tricky and should be treated with care! White is trying to play the Catalan, but we can't respond with our usual capture on c4, as White did not put a pawn there yet.  3.Bg5  makes no sense in our move order.  3...Be7  4.Bxe7  Qxe7=  and as is often the case in such positions, the most likely thing to happen is we get positions similar to 3.Nf3 / 4.Bg5, but without having wasted time playing ...a6. }
