8. Bg5
{ This does not really disturb us as the bishop soon has to move again. } 8...
Qb8 9. Qxc4 h6 10. Bf4 Bd6
{ Followed by ...Ngf6 and ...O-O, eventually followed by the liberating ...c5. Again, the main danger in such positions is not being able to develop the light squared bishop, but here it is very comfortable on b7. }
11. Nc3 Ngf6
{ We are ready to castle. After that, we'll start to fight back in the centre with moves like ...b5 and ...c5. }
