6. c3 Ne7 7. Bd3 O-O
{ 7...Ba6??  8.Bxa6  Nxa6  9.Qa4+  is an important trick to remember! } 8. O-O
Ba6 { Now everything is ready for this. } 9. Bxa6 Nxa6 10. Qd3
{ The only dangerous attempt. } 10... Nb8 11. Ng5
{ Here we should exercise some care. } 11... Nf5
{ 11...Ng6  12.h4!  is a bit unpleasant, although no big deal either.  12...Re8  13.h5  Nf8  is somewhat more passive but still reasonable. }
12. g4 h6 { The complications work out very well for us. } 13. gxf5 hxg5 14.
fxe6 Qf6
{ White's king is more vulnerable than ours. For instance :  15.exf7+  Rxf7  16.fxg5  Qxg5+  17.Qg3  Qh6!  followed by  Rf6  , with nice counterplay against White's king. }
