[Black "Exercise #5 "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2qk2r/1ppn1pp1/p2bbn1p/3p4/3P1P1B/2NBP3/PP4PP/R2QK1NR b KQkq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White has played quite aggressively with f4, and if they manage to stabilise the position with Nf3 and maybe even O-O, all the space on the kingside is likely to be unpleasant for us. We have to do something drastic to counter White's play - what's the solution? }
1... g5
{ Making use of our slight lead in development, and also that White has weakened their position a bit with f4! Engine prefers  1...Nb6  but not by much. }
2. fxg5 hxg5 3. Bxg5 Rxh2
{ 3...Bxh2  is also a good option, and in fact, the one recommended in thecourse! after which the position is quite messy, where White has a pin on the h file but worse pawn structure, and we are trying to get our king to safety on the queenside! We have to go into the complications after 1...g5 however, or we would definitely get squeezed! However, the engine prefers Rxh2, so I made it the solution to this puzzle just to show you have options. }
