[Black "Exercise #6 "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbq1rk1/p1p1nppp/1p2p3/3p4/3P1P2/2PB1N2/PP2QPPP/RN2K2R b KQ - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White played Qe2 for a reason, but we need to play accurately to relieve some of the pressure from our position. What is the best method of doing so? }
1... a5
{ We need to trade the bishops! Our passive c8 bishop is blocked by our pawns, and White's bishop in the centre is very active. White can't really stop ... Ba6 and the trade from happening now that both the knight and rook defend a6! Once the trade happens, we can start our own play with ...c5! Continue Studyinghere! }
