[FEN "r4rk1/2p1nppp/pp1q1n2/3p1b2/1P1P4/1Q3NP1/P2NPPBP/2R2RK1 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Due to the clumsy knight on c2, we are intending to initiate some play on the queenside. We have to initiate play in an accurate fashion however, what's our key strategic idea? }
1... c6
{ After a later ...a5 followed by White playing b5, we get much faster counterplay than starting with ...a5!   If  1...a5  2.b5  and we risk getting a weak pawn on c7! }
2. Ne5
{ White's last move was quite natural, getting the knight into the centre of the board, but we should stick with our idea! }
2... a5 3. b5
{ Allows us to show the full strength of our idea!   If  3.a3  we play  3...axb4  and now we have the a-file, giving us strong counterplay! }
3... cxb5 4. Qxb5 Qb4 5. Qxb4 axb4
{ We are now likely to just win the pawn on a2, and White can't attack our b pawn on b1 thanks to our strong bishop on f4! Black is doing very well here. Continue Studyinghere! }
