[FEN "1rbq1rk1/2p1bppp/p1n2n2/1p1pP3/2p5/2N2NP1/PP2QPBP/R1BR2K1 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ We have a difficult position to work out the correct continuation here - we are already up a few pawns, how should we proceed? }
1... d4
{ Allowing White to take our knight! After:  1...Ng4  If we move the knight, White takes d5  2.Nxd5  and the knight on d5 is now incredibly strong, leaving White with a serious initiative.   1...Nxe5  The engine seems to prefer losing this knight! }
2. exf6
{ 2.Nxd4  Engine says this is clearly better for White, and it's really hard to argue against it given the attack. }
2... Bxf6
{ Trading the piece off for 3 pawns and a very strong centre, where the d and c pawns are impossible to attack! Excellent compensation for the sacrificed piece, White lacks initiative and we have an unclear yet promising position! This can be tricky terrain to navigate, so please continue studyinghere! }
