[SetUp "1"]

{ We have a very strong knight on e4 and our bishops are pointing towards the White king, what's the best way to launch a kingside attack? }
1... h5
{ The point is to drive the knight away and keep pushing the pawn, creating weaknesses in the White camp! }
2. Rc2 h4 3. Nf1 h3
{ Matlakov even played this to provoke a further weakness! } 4. g3
{ The squares around the White king are weak, how should we try to open up the position for another one of our pieces? }
4... c5
{ Our bishop now stares down the long diagonal towards the White king. Matlakov held a nice advantage for the game and eventually converted into a win! Piasetski, L. - Matlakov, M. Gibraltar Masters, 2017. Review similar lines in thetheoretical section }
